<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,1917,2011]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1437,151,1979]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1917,1942]" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
No reliable morphological characters are known so far to separate the females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1218,1351,1918,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis box="[1218,1351,1918,1941]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaei" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">H. nicolaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[247,359,1952,1975]" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
The description of the female of 
<taxonomicName box="[728,857,1953,1976]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis box="[728,857,1953,1976]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
below is based on specimens from localities, where only males of 
<taxonomicName box="[311,442,1988,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis box="[311,442,1988,2011]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but no males of 
<taxonomicName box="[632,757,1987,2011]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaei">
<emphasis box="[632,757,1987,2011]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">H. nicolaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were collected. For characters distinguishing these two species from the females of other 
<taxonomicName authority="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1825" authorityName="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1825" box="[490,611,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthocopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[490,611,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Anthocopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species see under 
<taxonomicName box="[818,942,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaei">
<emphasis box="[818,942,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. nicolaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The male of 
<taxonomicName box="[1096,1226,153,176]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis box="[1096,1226,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognizable amongst the southeastern European 
<taxonomicName authority="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville, 1825" authorityName="Lepeletier &amp; Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1825" box="[625,747,187,211]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthocopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[625,747,187,211]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">Anthocopa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species by the shape of tergum 
<number box="[1128,1144,187,210]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" value="7.0">7</number>
, which is edged laterally almost at right angles and endowed medially with two moderately long teeth (
<figureCitation box="[1018,1101,221,245]" captionStart="FIGURE 17 – 24. 17" captionStartId="6.[151,249,1713,1736]" captionTargetBox="[151,1433,180,1687]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,179,1691]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 17 – 24. 17: Hoplitis nicolaei spec. nov., terga 5 – 7 of ɗ. 18: Hoplitis nicolaei spec. nov., genitalia of ɗ. 19: Hoplitis peniculifera spec. nov., apical margin of clypeus of Ψ. 20: Hoplitis peniculifera spec. nov., sterna 2 – 6 of ɗ. 21: Hoplitis serainae spec. nov., terga 5 – 7 of ɗ. 22: Hoplitis serainae spec. nov., genitalia of ɗ. 23: Hoplitis hilbera spec. nov., antenna of ɗ. 24: Hoplitis hilbera spec. nov., appendage of sternum 6 and tergum 7 of ɗ." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/281578/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[1070,1101,221,245]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" value="21.0">21</number>
</figureCitation>
). These teeth are only slightly longer than wide and separated from each other by a semicircular incision, which is about as wide as the basal diameter of one tooth. Apart from the shape of tergum 
<number box="[773,787,291,314]" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" value="7.0">7</number>
and the gonoforceps, the male of 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1306,292,315]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serainae">
<emphasis box="[1174,1306,292,315]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. serainae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically nearly identical to 
<taxonomicName box="[465,589,325,349]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Hoplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="45" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nicolaei">
<emphasis box="[465,589,325,349]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="45">H. nicolaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
